			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Soft water</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">软水（碳酸钙含量少</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Water with low mineral content</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Water with low mineral content</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Water</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>7732-18-5</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Soft water is water that is free from dissolved salts of metals such as calcium, iron, or magnesium. It is water with a very low mineral content, typically defined as less than 1 GPG. Water above this threshold is considered hard. Soft water is gentler on the skin and hair. It contains low amounts of ions like calcium and magnesium and is called 'soft' because of its simple composition. It doesn't leave scale inside appliances, and reduces the amount of water needed in dishwashers and washing machines.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">软水是不含钙、铁或镁等金属溶解盐的水。软水的矿物质含量非常低，通常小于 1 GPG。超过这一临界值的水被认为是硬水。软水对皮肤和头发更温和。它含有少量的钙和镁等离子，因其成分简单而被称为 &quot;软水&quot;。它不会在器具内留下水垢，并能减少洗碗机和洗衣机的用水量。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>H2O</sumFormula>
